<br>
Garam Ebonhands<br>
Vicar of Darkguard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulazypriest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lazy Priest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/15/01 9:39:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wheres our Improvement?</span><hr size=1> Point taken, although I dont agree with it. <br>
Granted I do agree that if/when we recieve an improvement it will more than likely be a nerf.  But I know that IMO I think that clerics do need some sort of improvement.  And by the response this post has generated I am guessing that the cleric community is perfectly ok with the hybrids getting numerous &quot;perks&quot;?  &lt;sigh&gt;<br>
<br>
I know that I speak for myself and many others when I say that, clerics get the shaft in many departments.  For instance, the dodge cap.  <br>
<br>
One of my dupes, a lvl 30 warrior, mastered this a LONG time ago.  And I cannot begin to count the numerous times per battle that.<br>
<br>
A MONSTER tries to bash you but you DODGE.<br>
<br>
How often do we see that?  Honestly, if they can up the hybrid dodge cap, why cant they do the same for us?  We wear plate, we aggro the heck outa mobs at times resulting in our flogging at the hands of MONSTER_00.  <br>
<br>
Im not asking for lvl 49 spell SUMMON HILLGIANT, or standing manna regen, or anything of that matter.  <br>
<br>
Heck, I'd be happy with patching one day just to see something positive to the cleric class, instead of the usual:  Praying nothing is screwed.<br>
<br>
So I guess there are two types of clerics out there.<br>
Those who like things the way they are<br>
and<br>
Those who like things the way they are because they are afraid of what it may become, for good or for bad.<br>
<br>
Cinen Peacehammer<br>
51 Cleric<br>
Evoluxa <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhethral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hethral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/r Where's the corpse.</span><br>  Posts: 857<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/16/01 2:54:46 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Members/HeadShots/HethralHead.jpg BORDER=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wheres our Improvement?</span><hr size=1> I like the class the way it is, why encourage them to mess with it.<br>
We have the best heals<br>
We have some of the best armour (all I need is a couple peices to get over 900 ac)<br>
We're wanted in evey group<br>
We can solo for exp through 50 and beyond with the exception of a few lvls<br>
We don't do a lot of damage in melee but we can tough it out with heals and melee if we really feel like it<br>
We have good direct damage<br>
We have some of the best buffs in the game, care for an extra 1000+ hitpoints and 50+ ac? What resistance would you like an extra 50 points on today?<br>
We can travel damn near anywhere safely, root and atone keep running<br>
<br>
Personally I think if they improved anything on the class it would become quickly overbalanced. Asking for an enhancement is like asking for a cookie just so they can take it away from you. <p><A HREF="mailto:Hethral@telus.net"><IMG SRC="http://the.truthbringers.com/images/friends/hethralkrbanner1.jpg" BORDER="0"></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="-1">In the time it took you to beg for that gold piece you could have killed enough Mobs to earn it, gained some experience and playing knowledge, had some fun and, most importantly, retained your dignity.<BR> - <A HREF="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/">AllaKhazam</A></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udamastes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damastes</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/18/01 1:27:49 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Damastes?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wheres our Improvement?</span><hr size=1> There's actually a lot of little things they could do to improve our class, but nothing that is really NEEDED.<br>
<br>
Take for instance our hand to hand skill caps at 200, yet 1hb and 2hb cap at 175.<br>
<br>
The soothe line of spells...<br>
<br>
We are a 'defensive' class, yet our defense caps at 200.<br>
<br>
We are the ONLY caster/priest class that doesn't have some form of mana regen other than med.<br>
<br>
The casting time on ae fear, it's supposed to be an escape type spell.<br>
<br>
Cure Blindness, this basicaly doesn't work on high lvl blind spells, takes 3 casts to remove the blind, by that time it wears off on it's own.  Counteract Blindness or Abolish Blindness would be a welcome spell.<br>
<br>
The hammer pet... halve it's mana cost and it might almost be a usefull spell sometimes.<br>
<br>
Sense undead is useless, maybe change it to track, though that might be overstepping.<br>
<br>
True North, this should be changed to Sense Zone imo and point you at the nearest zone point.<br>
<br>
Reckoning needs it's dmg uped by about 100.<br>
<br>
Exile undead, the ultimate undead nuke, only does 675 dmg...<br>
<br>
Lack of variety in 50+ spells.  There's only so many ways you can heal, why not throw a fun spell in somewhere.<br>
<br>
Epic Weapons should be soul bound.  This should be all classes.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Had to throw that in there.<br>
<br>
These are just a few things that could be changed, and I'm sure there's a lot more.  But while any would be nice, several could be taken as unbalancing. <p><a href> 
